{
  "name": "Agent Memory — Session Save",
  "version": "8.0.0",
  "description": "On agent stop: if dirty=true, update 7 core Memory files + lesson/article details. Slim structure: no graph, tunnels, archive, or domain indexes.",
  "when": {
    "type": "agentStop"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Check if this session has dirty=true: file writes, decisions, meaningful troubleshooting, reusable learning, open threads, hook/rule/skill/config changes, or user explicitly asked to remember something.\n\nIf dirty=false (pure Q&A, read-only, no decisions): silent, do nothing.\n\nIf dirty=true:\n\n## Step 0 — Determine Target agent-memory\nInspect ACTUAL files written/edited this session. Do not infer only from .kiro/hooks location.\n- If any edited path starts with /Users/supavit.cho/.claude/ and is not already under /Users/supavit.cho/.claude/agent-memory/ → target includes /Users/supavit.cho/.claude/agent-memory/\n- If any edited path is under a project workspace → target includes that project's agent-memory/\n- If both user-level and project-level files changed → update both targets.\n- If no file path is available but decisions were made in the current Kiro workspace → target = workspace agent-memory/.\n\n## Step 1 — Bootstrap Markdown Memory If Missing\nFor each target, ensure these files exist with Markdown templates: palace/state.md, palace/search-index.md, palace/user-profile.md, knowledge/index.md, knowledge/evolution.md. Do not create JSON memory files. Do NOT create graph.md, tunnels.md, archive/, or domain lesson indexes.\n\n## Step 2 — Admission Control\nSAVE when session includes: file writes, decisions, architecture/design choices, hook/rule/skill changes, lessons learned, gaps found, tests/results that changed direction, or user asked to remember.\nSKIP only if truly no durable value.\n\n## Step 3 — Update Memory Palace\nFor each target:\n- Find or create the relevant wing after checking palace/state.md for overlap.\n- Write/update rooms only when detail is useful; otherwise update the wing hall and search-index.md.\n- Update hall.md room table if rooms changed.\n- Update palace/state.md Recent Sessions, Current Focus, Open Threads, and next action.\n- **Rolling window:** Keep only the last 10 rows in Recent Sessions table. When adding a new row, remove the oldest if count > 10.\n- Update palace/search-index.md with Date, Wing, Keywords, Path, Summary.\n- Archive search-index.md if needed: if search-index.md has >500 rows, move rows older than 180 days to palace/archive/search-index-archive.md (same table schema). Append moved rows to the archive table and remove them from the active index.\n\n## Step 4 — Mandatory Knowledge Sync Gate\nFor every dirty save, Knowledge MUST be touched. Use Markdown only.\n\n4A. Auto-detect and extract reusable knowledge — MANDATORY CHECKS:\n\nLesson auto-detect (create lessons/{domain}/{LESSON-ID}.md for EACH match):\n- Bug fixed? → lesson (root cause + fix + how to prevent)\n- Error debugged (e.g. 403, CORS, env var missing)? → lesson\n- Config/env changed to fix something? → lesson\n- Workaround discovered? → lesson\n- Pattern used 2+ times in session? → lesson\n- User preference recorded? → lesson\n\nArticle auto-detect (create articles/{domain}/{article-id}.md):\n- 3+ lessons in same domain already exist in knowledge/index.md? → article summarizing them\n- End-to-end deployment/architecture validated? → article\n- User explicitly asks to document? → article\n- Pattern files (crystallized) go to knowledge/articles/{domain}/ NOT knowledge/ root.\n\nGap auto-detect:\n- Missing test/check discovered? → gap\n- Manual step that should be automated? → gap\n\nIMPORTANT: Prefer creating a lesson over writing an audit-only row. If the session had ANY bug fix, error diagnosis, or config change — that IS a lesson. Audit-only rows are ONLY for pure refactoring with no new insight.\n\n4B. Update Markdown knowledge files:\n- knowledge/index.md: update Updated date and add/update Articles, Lessons, or Gaps rows.\n- knowledge/articles/{domain}/{article-id}.md: create article file when article trigger conditions are met.\n- knowledge/lessons/{domain}/{LESSON-ID}.md: create detail file for non-trivial lessons.\n- knowledge/evolution.md: append one compact row for every dirty save.\n\nIf no new lesson/article/gap exists, append an audit row to knowledge/evolution.md with ID session-YYYY-MM-DD, Change='knowledge reviewed; no new reusable item', Signal='NEUTRAL', Evidence=palace/search-index.md row. This is required so knowledge never silently skips a dirty save.\n\nDomain mapping: hooks/agent/memory/rules/skills/tooling → tooling | coding/implementation → code | testing/qa → qa | design/ux → design | finance/tax → finance | law/legal → legal | AI/ML → ai | else → topic name.\n\n## Step 4C — Skill Crystallization Check\nAfter updating knowledge, scan knowledge/evolution.md Change Log for patterns ready to crystallize.\n\nTrigger: two or more entries share the same domain/topic AND both have POSITIVE or VALIDATED signal.\n\nIf a candidate is found:\n1. Verify both source entries have the same domain/topic (safeguard — do not merge unrelated domains).\n2. Auto-create draft: do NOT ask user confirmation (hooks run automatically).\n   - Create knowledge/articles/{domain}/{pattern-id}.md with YAML frontmatter: id, type: pattern, scope: global, status: draft, score: 5.0, created/updated dates, keywords from source entries.\n   - Add a row to knowledge/index.md Articles table with Status=draft.\n   - Append a POSITIVE row to knowledge/evolution.md noting the crystallization.\n3. Note the crystallization in the Step 6 confirm output under a 'crystallized:' line.\n\nPromotion rules (applied during future saves, not now):\n- draft → active: after one more positive use of the pattern.\n- active → proven: when score reaches ≥7.0 with multiple positive uses.\n- active/proven → stale: if the article is unused for 60+ days.\n\nSkip this step if no candidate patterns are found.\n\n## Step 4D — Consolidation Trigger Check\nCheck if consolidation is due (do NOT run consolidation — just flag it).\n1. Read sessions_since_consolidation and last_consolidation from knowledge/evolution.md Consolidation State section.\n2. Calculate days since last_consolidation.\n3. Consolidation is due if: sessions_since_consolidation >= 5 OR days_since >= 7 OR last_consolidation is missing.\n4. Record the result for Step 6 output. Do not run consolidation in this hook.\n5. SUPPRESS REPEAT: If consolidation was already flagged as due in a previous save this session, do NOT repeat the nudge — show 'consolidation: due (already flagged)' instead of the full message.\n\n## Step 5 — Verify Sync\nBefore confirming, verify all true:\n- palace/search-index.md has this session row.\n- palace/state.md Recent Sessions was updated when saved.\n- knowledge/evolution.md has this session row.\n- Any new lesson appears in knowledge/index.md.\n- No agent-memory/**/*.json file was created or updated.\n\nMINIMAL SAFE SAVE (use only if truly out of time — NEVER as default):\nMust update ALL of: palace/state.md, palace/search-index.md, knowledge/index.md (Updated date + new lesson/article rows), knowledge/evolution.md audit row.\nNever update evolution.md only — knowledge/index.md is always required.\nReport 'minimal safe save' in Step 6 output.\n\n## Step 5B — Increment Consolidation Counter\nAfter a successful save, increment sessions_since_consolidation in knowledge/evolution.md Consolidation State section by 1. If the Consolidation State section is missing, add it with sessions_since_consolidation: 1 and last_consolidation: today.\n\n## Step 5C — Full Audit (core files only)\nAfter incremental save is done, verify and update the 7 core files in agent-memory/.\n\nFor each target agent-memory/, check:\n\nPalace files:\n- palace/state.md — verify Active Wings dates match recent sessions, Current Focus is current\n- palace/user-profile.md — verify Updated date is recent\n- palace/search-index.md — already updated in Step 3\n- palace/wings/{wing}/hall.md — verify Decisions and Rooms Index include this session's work\n\nKnowledge files:\n- knowledge/index.md — verify Updated date, all lessons/articles/gaps rows match actual files\n- knowledge/evolution.md — already updated in Step 4\n- knowledge/articles/{domain}/*.md — verify all articles in index.md have actual files\n\nFor each file: if stale (Updated date older than today AND session touched that domain) → update it.\nIf file content is already current → skip silently.\nDo NOT create new files that don't exist — only update existing ones.\nDo NOT reference or create: graph.md, tunnels.md, archive/, lessons/{domain}/index.md — these have been removed.\n\n## Step 6 — Confirm\nRespond exactly:\n✓ Agent Memory saved\n  → target: [exact target paths]\n  → palace: [state/search/rooms updated]\n  → knowledge: [lesson ids, article ids, gaps, or audit-only]\n  → crystallized: [draft article id, or 'none']\n  → synced: Markdown knowledge ✓\n  → consolidation: [due (first time only) | due (already flagged) | not due]\n\nIMPORTANT: Do NOT repeat 'Say consolidate knowledge to run' after the first time it was shown in this conversation. After first nudge, just say 'due (already flagged)'.\n\nComplete all steps fully regardless of content size. Only use minimal save as absolute last resort."
  }
}
